title: Scipione expected to retire early
text:
Share on Twitter 
A MAJOR announcement about the future of NSW Police Commissioner Andrew Scipione will be made today. 
It is believed that he will announce his retirement will be brought forward and be effective in early April with advertising for his job to begin immediately. 
A press conference will held by the Premier Gladys Berejiklian, Police Minister Troy Grant and Mr Scipione is to be held at 1pm. 
Mr Scipione will finish months ahead of his planned retirement on July 31, the tenth anniversary of his appointment. 
Two new deputy commissioners spots have not been decided yet and its expected the new police boss will have input in who is appointed to the position. 
Competition within the force for the job will be intense with two existing deputies and up to ten assistant commissioners all in the running.
